Identified Weakness:

The rule detects individual destructive commands but does not correlate multiple ransomware precursor actions within a time window, resulting in fragmented low-confidence alerts.

Before (Existing Rule):
DeviceProcessEvents
| where TimeGenerated > ago(30m)
| where ProcessCommandLine has_any ("vssadmin delete shadows", "wbadmin delete catalog", "bcdedit /set")
| where InitiatingProcessAccountName !in ("SYSTEM", "TrustedInstaller")
| summarize CommandCount = count() by DeviceName, InitiatingProcessAccountName, bin(TimeGenerated, 5m)
| where CommandCount >= 1

After (Improved Rule):
DeviceProcessEvents
| where TimeGenerated > ago(30m) // Focus on recent activity window
| where ProcessCommandLine has_any (
    "net.exe view",                // Enumeration precursor
    "vssadmin delete shadows",    // Shadow copy deletion
    "wbadmin delete catalog",     // Backup catalog removal
    "bcdedit /set"                // Recovery disable
)
| where InitiatingProcessAccountName !in ("SYSTEM", "TrustedInstaller") // Reduce system noise
| summarize 
    CommandSet = make_set(ProcessCommandLine), 
    CommandCount = dcount(ProcessCommandLine),
    StartTime = min(TimeGenerated),
    EndTime = max(TimeGenerated)
    by DeviceName, InitiatingProcessAccountName
| where CommandCount >= 3 // Require multiple distinct behaviors (ransomware staging pattern)
| extend TimeWindow = datetime_diff("minute", EndTime, StartTime)
| where TimeWindow <= 30 // Ensure activity occurs in short sequence (behavioral correlation)

Explanation:
Detection accuracy: Moves from single-event detection to multi-stage behavioral correlation, aligning with actual ransomware playbook observed in the incident
Noise reduction: Eliminates benign single-command executions by requiring multiple distinct high-risk actions within a defined window
Earlier detection: Includes enumeration (net.exe) along with destructive commands, enabling detection during staging phase before encryption begins